The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 15 November is 7,882 (912.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 November, there were 994 new confirmed cases (115.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 November, there were 855 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 16% ( 139 extra cases).
